title: Independent candidate Fazal Elahi wins PK-84 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Fazal Elahi has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-84, Peshawar-XIII by securing 25,850 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party (ANP) Farhad Khan who bagged 8,248 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 34.82 percent.
